
[1]pharisee

   PHAR'ISEE, n. [Heb. to separate.] One of a sect among the Jews, whose
   religion consisted in a strict observance of rites and ceremonies and
   of the traditions of the elders,and whose pretended holiness led them
   to separate themselves as a sect, considering themselves as more
   righteous than other Jews.
